2.title: Cajun Caviar
2.plot: P'Maw makes a promise to a comely customer who wants him to find rare fish eggs in the heat of summer; Corey and T-Monkey fight over the night shift at the shop.

3.title: Goat Wedding
3.plot: P'Maw wants to make jambalaya with an animal he hit with his car, but first has to send Ricky and T-Monkey to find it. Meanwhile, a goat wedding at the shop has P'Maw playing matchmaker.

4.title: Gar Balls
4.plot: A home invasion by opossums forces T-Monkey to beg for help; P'Maw places a wager on the tastiest fish in the swamp.

5.title: Crab Infestation
5.plot: A fishing trip goes awry for Corey, Ricky and T-Monkey when they're stranded in the swamp; a crab problem could hurt P'Maw's business, but one of his customers may have a solution.

6.title: Croaked
6.plot: P'Maw's reputation is at stake when he makes two promises that he finds difficult to keep, including a stuffed bullfrog for one customer and 100 frogs for a party for another.
